Text.LocalizedString: Kelp is full of nutrients that can be beneficial to the environment.

Text.LocalizedString: For instance, the kelp forest is just like our forest.//It provides a stable home to many species.

Text.LocalizedString: An oil-drilling company has been looking into my lab’s work lately and asked me about the state of our coral reefs.//I think it could be the same company that’s moving in this Summer.

Text.LocalizedString: I always try to donate before Winter hits. Just whatever I knit that year.//Usually, the mayor and <NPCName>Bree</> have things for me to send too.

Text.LocalizedString: Aren’t you cold, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’m happy with the progress we’ve made this year.//I’m excited to see what the New Year brings to our island.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m happy with the progress we’ve made this year.//I’m excited to see what the New Year brings to our island.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m excited about the prospect of heat-resistant coral reefs.//I feel like it’ll make a massive difference in the ecosystem.

Text.SourceString: Of course, we need to fight pollution too.
Text.LocalizedString: Of course, we need to fight pollution too.

Text.LocalizedString: I wear the same beanie every year.//Why replace something that’s still good, right?

Text.LocalizedString: Seems like it’s snowing pretty hard outside.

Text.SourceString: Saturday is a good day to take off.
Text.LocalizedString: Saturday is a good day to take off.

Text.SourceString: Anyway, I can’t work my best if I don’t take a break every now and then.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, I can’t work my best if I don’t take a break every now and then.

Text.LocalizedString: Unfortunately, we need to keep the windows shut. I have to be sure there’s no contamination.

Text.SourceString: There’s no need for me to concentrate when I knit.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s no need for me to concentrate when I knit.

Text.SourceString: It’s kind of nice, actually. Especially after a long day of focusing on work.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kind of nice, actually. Especially after a long day of focusing on work.

Text.SourceString: Knitting helps keep your joints healthy. Did you know that?
Text.LocalizedString: Knitting helps keep your joints healthy. Did you know that?

Text.SourceString: It’s not just that. It also exercises your brain.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not just that. It also exercises your brain.

Text.SourceString: I almost always lived by myself when I was young, and I didn’t think I was lonely until I had company.
Text.LocalizedString: I almost always lived by myself when I was young, and I didn’t think I was lonely until I had company.

Text.SourceString: I guess I was so used to being alone I didn’t know any other way.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I was so used to being alone I didn’t know any other way.

Text.SourceString: I started to knit in grade school.
Text.LocalizedString: I started to knit in grade school.

Text.SourceString: I had a hard time concentrating on math homework until I started knitting while thinking about a problem.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a hard time concentrating on math homework until I started knitting while thinking about a problem.

Text.SourceString: I never found the time to redecorate this house. Good thing <NPCName>Leah</> gives it the attention it needs.
Text.LocalizedString: I never found the time to redecorate this house. Good thing <NPCName>Leah</> gives it the attention it needs.

Text.SourceString: This is all her, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: This is all her, you know.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> is very perceptive about beauty, fashion, and stuff like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> is very perceptive about beauty, fashion, and stuff like that.

Text.SourceString: A talent she inherited from her mother, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: A talent she inherited from her mother, I think.

Text.SourceString: Do you know <NPCName>Walter</> well? He used to practice law in the city.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know <NPCName>Walter</> well? He used to practice law in the city.

Text.SourceString: Oh, that was long before <NPCName>Luke</> was even born. I heard that’s where he met <NPCName>Bree</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, that was long before <NPCName>Luke</> was even born. I heard that’s where he met <NPCName>Bree</>.

Text.SourceString: It’s okay to unwind once in a while, but everything in moderation.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s okay to unwind once in a while, but everything in moderation.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to think about work in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to think about work in this weather.

Text.SourceString: I need to get my flu shot, with colder weather on the way. Better safe than sorry, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get my flu shot, with colder weather on the way. Better safe than sorry, I think.

Text.SourceString: *achoo!*
Text.LocalizedString: *achoo!*

Text.SourceString: I think I’ve got the flu, but I’m not sure. I’m going to see what <NPCName>Charles</> thinks.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ve got the flu, but I’m not sure. I’m going to see what <NPCName>Charles</> thinks.

Text.SourceString: Just in case, don’t get too close.
Text.LocalizedString: Just in case, don’t get too close.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Bree</>? Hmm. I don’t have a clue where she’d be.//We’re good friends, but that doesn’t mean I know where she is every minute.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Bree</>? Hmm. I don’t have a clue where she’d be.//We’re good friends, but that doesn’t mean I know where she is every minute.

Text.SourceString: Have you tried the vineyard?//She may be in the greenhouse, gardening.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried the vineyard?//She may be in the greenhouse, gardening.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I wonder if I should just make grilled vegetables for dinner again tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. I wonder if I should just make grilled vegetables for dinner again tonight.

Text.SourceString: Before I met <NPCName>Randy</>, I didn’t mind devoting my life solely to the study of coral reefs.//Day in and day out.
Text.LocalizedString: Before I met <NPCName>Randy</>, I didn’t mind devoting my life solely to the study of coral reefs.//Day in and day out.

Text.SourceString: I love my job. But now I have more than just a job to look forward to.//<portrait=normal>Feels strange. In a good way.
Text.LocalizedString: I love my job. But now I have more than just a job to look forward to.//<portrait=normal>Feels strange. In a good way.

Text.SourceString: There are pearls and lots of other things in the ocean you can collect and sell.//<portrait=happy>Not just kelp!
Text.LocalizedString: There are pearls and lots of other things in the ocean you can collect and sell.//<portrait=happy>Not just kelp!

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Leah</>, she should be leading a yoga class in the community center today.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Leah</>, she should be leading a yoga class in the community center today.

Text.SourceString: She’s a busy girl.//If she’s not there, then I really can’t tell you where she’d be. Sorry.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s a busy girl.//If she’s not there, then I really can’t tell you where she’d be. Sorry.

Text.SourceString: I buy my coffee beans from <NPCName>Sam</>.//They’re okay.
Text.LocalizedString: I buy my coffee beans from <NPCName>Sam</>.//They’re okay.

Text.SourceString: The coffee from <NPCName>Raj</>’s probably tastes better, but I don’t want to spend hundreds of coins for a cup of coffee every day.//The normal kind does the job fine.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee from <NPCName>Raj</>’s probably tastes better, but I don’t want to spend hundreds of coins for a cup of coffee every day.//The normal kind does the job fine.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I wonder if I should just make grilled vegetables again tonight.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Leah</> might have taken care of dinner already.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. I wonder if I should just make grilled vegetables again tonight.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Leah</> might have taken care of dinner already.

Text.SourceString: I came down here to work as soon as I got my degree.//I knew this was my future from the get-go.
Text.LocalizedString: I came down here to work as soon as I got my degree.//I knew this was my future from the get-go.

Text.SourceString: And I still do.//<portrait=normal>Years later, a lot has changed – but at the same time, nothing has changed.
Text.LocalizedString: And I still do.//<portrait=normal>Years later, a lot has changed – but at the same time, nothing has changed.

Text.SourceString: Knitting can elevate your mood and improve your motor function.//<portrait=happy>It’s a great hobby!
Text.LocalizedString: Knitting can elevate your mood and improve your motor function.//<portrait=happy>It’s a great hobby!

Text.SourceString: Besides, it gives my brain a bit of a break.//Even watching TV is too tiring for me sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, it gives my brain a bit of a break.//Even watching TV is too tiring for me sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I’d take an exceptional bottle of kelp over wine.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d take an exceptional bottle of kelp over wine.

Text.SourceString: But I do enjoy wine from time to time.
Text.LocalizedString: But I do enjoy wine from time to time.

Text.SourceString: I’ve liked learning about hum–//<portrait=concerned>Umm…//<portrait=normal>About technology since I was little.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve liked learning about hum–//<portrait=concerned>Umm…//<portrait=normal>About technology since I was little.

Text.SourceString: All I did was read and build things. At the time, I wasn’t sure what I was going to end up with.//But I was always building something.
Text.LocalizedString: All I did was read and build things. At the time, I wasn’t sure what I was going to end up with.//But I was always building something.

Text.SourceString: Studying coral reefs yesterday, I felt like an eager new student.//Now, my hip hurts from standing too much.
Text.LocalizedString: Studying coral reefs yesterday, I felt like an eager new student.//Now, my hip hurts from standing too much.

Text.SourceString: Where did all the years go, I wonder?
Text.LocalizedString: Where did all the years go, I wonder?

Text.SourceString: Wow! I can’t believe it’s Sunday again!
Text.LocalizedString: Wow! I can’t believe it’s Sunday again!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> is a lovely young lady.//She may seem detached from reality sometimes, but she has a good heart.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> is a lovely young lady.//She may seem detached from reality sometimes, but she has a good heart.

Text.SourceString: Errr, it really isn’t my place to comment, but she had a rough childhood.//I think that’s why she’s the way she is now.
Text.LocalizedString: Errr, it really isn’t my place to comment, but she had a rough childhood.//I think that’s why she’s the way she is now.

Text.SourceString: I encourage <NPCName>Randy</> to try to have a better relationship with <NPCName>Leah’s</> mother.//I think it would be good for all of them.
Text.LocalizedString: I encourage <NPCName>Randy</> to try to have a better relationship with <NPCName>Leah’s</> mother.//I think it would be good for all of them.

Text.SourceString: It must have been hard for that poor girl to grow up in the middle of a divorce.
Text.LocalizedString: It must have been hard for that poor girl to grow up in the middle of a divorce.

Text.SourceString: When I first came here to live, I thought I’d want to visit my home more, but I’m shocked that I don’t.//I do miss it every once in a while, but not as much as I thought I would.
Text.LocalizedString: When I first came here to live, I thought I’d want to visit my home more, but I’m shocked that I don’t.//I do miss it every once in a while, but not as much as I thought I would.

Text.SourceString: What brings you to this part of the island, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: What brings you to this part of the island, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The weekend?

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Hang on.//<portrait=concerned>Hang on…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Hang on.//<portrait=concerned>Hang on…

Text.SourceString: Am I hearing things?
Text.LocalizedString: Am I hearing things?

Text.SourceString: I’m not working today. So, here I am.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not working today. So, here I am.

Text.SourceString: As my husband puts it, I’m <Italic>living</> a little.
Text.LocalizedString: As my husband puts it, I’m <Italic>living</> a little.

Text.SourceString: I never found the time to redecorate this house. Good thing <NPCName>Leah</> gives it the attention it needs.
Text.LocalizedString: I never found the time to redecorate this house. Good thing <NPCName>Leah</> gives it the attention it needs.

Text.SourceString: This is all her, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: This is all her, you know.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> is very perceptive about beauty, fashion, and stuff like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> is very perceptive about beauty, fashion, and stuff like that.

Text.SourceString: A talent she inherited from her mother, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: A talent she inherited from her mother, I think.

Text.SourceString: I never found the time to redecorate our house. This job requires me to be here all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: I never found the time to redecorate our house. This job requires me to be here all the time.

Text.SourceString: Good thing <NPCName>Leah</> gives it the attention it needs.//That is all her, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing <NPCName>Leah</> gives it the attention it needs.//That is all her, you know.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah</> is very perceptive about beauty, fashion, and stuff like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah</> is very perceptive about beauty, fashion, and stuff like that.

Text.SourceString: A talent she inherited from her mother, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: A talent she inherited from her mother, I think.

Text.SourceString: Careful what you touch here, will you?
Text.LocalizedString: Careful what you touch here, will you?

Text.SourceString: We rarely get visitors.//I invited <NPCName>Randy</> to bring the kids. He brought them a couple of times, years ago, but never since.//<portrait=concerned>Not many things to look at, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: We rarely get visitors.//I invited <NPCName>Randy</> to bring the kids. He brought them a couple of times, years ago, but never since.//<portrait=concerned>Not many things to look at, huh?

Text.SourceString: The water in the tank has the same salinity as the ocean.//In fact, it has the same exact composition.
Text.LocalizedString: The water in the tank has the same salinity as the ocean.//In fact, it has the same exact composition.

Text.SourceString: Our filter broke a couple years back. Turned out there was a soggy kite stuck in it.//<portrait=annoyed>Yeah, the one outside. That was a pain to fix.
Text.LocalizedString: Our filter broke a couple years back. Turned out there was a soggy kite stuck in it.//<portrait=annoyed>Yeah, the one outside. That was a pain to fix.

Text.SourceString: I prefer to have my lunch outside in the little park across from the lab.//<portrait=annoyed>The smell of chemicals and salt are too strong in here. It kills my appetite.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to have my lunch outside in the little park across from the lab.//<portrait=annoyed>The smell of chemicals and salt are too strong in here. It kills my appetite.

Text.SourceString: I crocheted this hat.//<portrait=normal>Made about a dozen or so. I sent them to a homeless shelter in Pokyo last week.
Text.LocalizedString: I crocheted this hat.//<portrait=normal>Made about a dozen or so. I sent them to a homeless shelter in Pokyo last week.

Text.SourceString: I brought an extra layer, just in case it gets windy.//You never know.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought an extra layer, just in case it gets windy.//You never know.

Text.SourceString: I purchased these sweatpants at White Flamingo.//<portrait=happy>They’re very comfortable. I might start wearing them all the time!
Text.LocalizedString: I purchased these sweatpants at White Flamingo.//<portrait=happy>They’re very comfortable. I might start wearing them all the time!

Text.SourceString: Where I’m from, it’s often dark like this. This lab reminds me a lot of where I grew up.//Especially the colorful corals.
Text.LocalizedString: Where I’m from, it’s often dark like this. This lab reminds me a lot of where I grew up.//Especially the colorful corals.

Text.SourceString: What’s on your mind?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s on your mind?

Text.SourceString: I helped bu–//<portrait=annoyed>Er, I’m a scientist. I know a lot about a lot of things.
Text.LocalizedString: I helped bu–//<portrait=annoyed>Er, I’m a scientist. I know a lot about a lot of things.

Special.SourceString: How do you know so much about merfolk technology?
Special.LocalizedString: How do you know so much about merfolk technology?

191.SpecialTag: How do you know so much about merfolk technology?
191.Question: R1

Text.SourceString: Yes, but ocean water doesn’t agree with my skin.//I think I’ll stick to fresh water for now.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, but ocean water doesn’t agree with my skin.//I think I’ll stick to fresh water for now.

Text.SourceString: Of course! I used to live there!//<portrait=annoyed>Er, I mean I studied it so much, I practically lived there. That’s a saying, I think. Yeah!
Text.LocalizedString: Of course! I used to live there!//<portrait=annoyed>Er, I mean I studied it so much, I practically lived there. That’s a saying, I think. Yeah!

Special.SourceString: You seem to know a lot about the ocean.
Special.LocalizedString: You seem to know a lot about the ocean.

193.SpecialTag: You seem to know a lot about the ocean.
193.Question: R3

Text.SourceString: The cute little lobster, the one that’s always with <NPCName>Macy</>, reminds me of an old friend’s pet.
Text.LocalizedString: The cute little lobster, the one that’s always with <NPCName>Macy</>, reminds me of an old friend’s pet.

Text.SourceString: He also had a pet lobster, blue like that too.//<portrait=normal>He made a little throne for it. Even had its name engraved on it. Very cute!
Text.LocalizedString: He also had a pet lobster, blue like that too.//<portrait=normal>He made a little throne for it. Even had its name engraved on it. Very cute!

Text.SourceString: Is everything alright at the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: Is everything alright at the farm?

Text.SourceString: Once in a while, <NpcName>Surya</> and I take turns cleaning up the aquarium.//<portrait=annoyed>It's a pain.
Text.LocalizedString: Once in a while, <NpcName>Surya</> and I take turns cleaning up the aquarium.//<portrait=annoyed>It's a pain.

Text.SourceString: The Pet Day yesterday was a blast.//<portrait=happy>Who taught Bonbon to dance like that? What a smart puppy.
Text.LocalizedString: The Pet Day yesterday was a blast.//<portrait=happy>Who taught Bonbon to dance like that? What a smart puppy.

Text.SourceString: I should talk to <NpcName>Millie</> and see if I can help prepare the beach clean up festival.//It's coming very soon, isn't it? The 27th?
Text.LocalizedString: I should talk to <NpcName>Millie</> and see if I can help prepare the beach clean up festival.//It's coming very soon, isn't it? The 27th?

Text.SourceString: It was challenging to make <NPCName>Kible</>.//I failed several times. Good thing I could reuse some of the parts, so it wasn't a total waste.
Text.LocalizedString: It was challenging to make <NPCName>Kible</>.//I failed several times. Good thing I could reuse some of the parts, so it wasn't a total waste.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kible</>'s my baby. My proudest invention so far.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kible</>'s my baby. My proudest invention so far.
